==English==
=== Etymology ===
''[[nucleic]]'' (of the ''[[nucleus]]'') + ''[[acid]]''

=== Noun ===
{{wikipedia}}
#{{biochemistry}},{{genetics}} any [[acidic]], [[chainlike]] [[biological]] [[macromolecule]] consisting of multiply repeat units of [[phosphoric acid]], [[sugar]] and [[purine]] and [[pyrimidine]] [[base]]s; they are involved in the [[preservation]], [[replication]] and [[expression]] of [[hereditary]] [[information]] in every [[living]] [[cell]]

